      "content": "I hear you on the modeling aspects, but it feels like the \"growth\" benefits are a bit speculative compared to the actual, measurable impact of the capital gains stuff. If we look at the data from previous similar reforms, isn't it more accurate to say that the wealth concentration effect is basically a certainty while the supply-side stimulus is just a theory? It seems like one side has the math on their side.",
